{"ts":"2026-06-27T09:41:02.746Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"aenf1gd3","input":{"summary":"I have successfully verified, configured, and validated the local FastAPI backend folder and developer setup for the GFF AI platform.\n\n### Files Created/Changed:\n1. **`backend/requirements.txt`**: Added standard, clean Python dependencies including `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `sqlalchemy`, `pydantic`, `pydantic-settings`, and `python-dotenv`.\n2. **`backend/app/`**:\n   - `main.py`: Configured the FastAPI application entry point with lifespan events, custom CORS policies, request timing middleware, and redirection to OpenAPI docs (`/docs`).\n   - `api.py`: Implemented robust `/api/v1/health` and `/api/v1/logs` endpoints.\n   - `database.py`: Created the SQLAlchemy SQLite engine configuration with session management and thread safety parameters.\n   - `models.py`: Created the relational `SystemLog` database model for development tracking.\n   - `schemas.py`: Defined clean Pydantic V2 schemas for input validation and serialized API response models.\n   - `config.py`: Set up environment variable validation via Pydantic Settings.\n3. **`backend/README.md`**: Standardized senior-grade operational execution manual for local python virtual environments and API verification.\n4. **`backend/.env.example`**: Outlined safe local development settings and placeholders.\n5. **`.gitignore`**: Prevented local development databases (`*.db`, `*.sqlite3`) and Python environments (`venv/`) from being accidentally committed.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- **Python Compilation**: Successfully compiled all Python files with `py_compile` under Python 3.12.0.\n- **Python Virtualenv Setup**: Spawned a Python virtualenv inside `backend/venv/`, updated pip, and successfully installed all backend dependencies.\n- **SQLite Database Bootstrapping and Operations**: Executed an end-to-end programmatic integration test to automatically bootstrap tables, check connections, perform INSERT operations, and query log results. Everything works flawlessly.\n- **Frontend Code Quality & Tools Logic**: Executed the frontend TypeScript linter (`npm run lint`) and the custom tools deterministic validation suite (`npm run verify-tools`), passing with 100% success.\n- **Zero Real Integration Leakage**: Confirmed that the Next.js app remains completely clean and free of third-party SaaS backend dependencies, AWS connections, or OTP email services, staying compliant with all security and architectural guardrails.\n\n### Limitations:\n- The backend is strictly configured as a local development MVP foundation utilizing SQLite. It does not contain any production database drivers, real SMTP, AWS credentials, or real third-party API keys, complying with the gff-ai-guardrails.","verified":true}}}
